  "title": "Warehouse Supervisor",
  "description": "<p>As a Warehouse Supervisor, you will play a pivotal role in overseeing the daily operations of our warehouse facility. You will be responsible for managing inventory, coordinating logistics, supervising staff, and ensuring a safe and efficient workflow.</p>\n<p><strong>Job Responsibilities</strong></p>\n<p>· Manage, support, plan and organise day-to-day inventory and all inventory control process within the warehouse to ensure smooth operations.</p>\n<p>· Ensure daily warehouse activities are performed in a timely, efficient and accurate manner.</p>\n<p>· Ensure proper and accurate placement of all goods</p>\n<p>· Support order fulfilment, picking, packing &amp; ensuring on time delivery of merchandise and minimal error in fulfilment orders</p>\n<p>· Provide leadership and guidance to the warehouse team (about 10 pax), including training, scheduling, and performance management</p>\n<p>· Work closely with retail operations and cross functional teams to resolve daily operational issues.</p>\n<p>· Continuously evaluate warehouse processes and identify opportunities for improvement to enhance efficiency and productivity.</p>\n<p>· Establish and maintain Standard Operation Procedures (SOP).</p>\n<p><strong>Job Requirements</strong></p>\n<p>· Qualifications in Logistic, Supply Chain Management or any related field.</p>\n<p>· Possess at least 3 years of supervisory experience in Retail Logistic, or Supply Chain.</p>\n<p>· Proficient in Microsoft Office, ERP/WMS experience is an added advantage</p>\n<p>· Demonstrated leadership abilities with a track record of effectively managing teams and fostering a positive work environment.</p>",
